[30;1m560 | [0m[35mclass StationaryPoissonProcess(RenewalProcess):[0m
[30;1m561 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m562 | [0m[35m    Generates spike trains whose spikes are realizations of a stationary[0m

[30;1m288 | [0m[35m    if len(cutout) == 0:[0m
[30;1m289 | [0m[35m        events_base = np.zeros(0)[0m
[30;1m290 | [0m[35m    else:[0m
[30;1m291 | [0m[35m        # Select thr crossings lasting at least 2 dtps, np.diff(cutout) > 2[0m
[30;1m292 | [0m[35m        # This avoids empty slices[0m
[30;1m293 | [0m[35m        border_start = np.where(np.diff(cutout) > 1)[0][0m
[30;1m294 | [0m[35m        border_end = border_start + 1[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mto Granger cause the other signal.[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mGranger causality analysis can be extended to the spectral domain investigating[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35mthe influnece signals have onto each other in a frequency resolved manner. It[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35mrelies on estimating the cross-spectrum of time series and decomposing them[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35minto a transfer function and a noise covariance matrix. The method to estimate[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35mthe spectral Granger causality is non-parametric in the sense that it does not[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35mrequire to fit an autoregressive model (see :cite:`granger-Dhamala08_354`).[0m

[30;1m401 | [0m[35m    Generates surrogates of a spike train by spike train shifting.[0m
[30;1m402 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m403 | [0m[35m    The surrogates are obtained by shifting the whole spike train by a[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35m"""[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mThe Change point detection algorithm :cite:`cpd-Messer2014_2027` determines if[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35ma spike train `spiketrain` can be considered as a stationary process (constant[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mfiring rate) or not as stationary process (i.e. presence of one or more points[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mat which the rate increases or decreases). In case of non-stationarity, the[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35moutput is a list of detected Change Points (CPs).[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mEssentially, a set of two-sided windows of width `h`[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m759[0m[34m of [0m[33m1142[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m135 | [0m[35m            cp = cp_index * dt_temp + h[0m
[30;1m136 | [0m[35m            # before repeating the procedure, the h-neighbourgs of detected CP[0m
[30;1m137 | [0m[35m            # are discarded, because rate changes into it are alrady explained[0m
[30;1m138 | [0m[35m            mask_fore = time_index > cp_index - int((h / dt_temp).simplified)[0m
[30;1m139 | [0m[35m            mask_back = time_index < cp_index + int((h / dt_temp).simplified)[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35m            differences[mask_fore & mask_back] = 0[0m

[30;1m169 | [0m[35m    It constructs a matrix G[i, j] containing the minimal cost when only[0m
[30;1m170 | [0m[35m    considering the first i and j spikes of the spike trains. However, one[0m
[30;1m171 | [0m[35m    never needs to store more than one row and one column at the same time[0m

[30;1m2 | [0m[35mGaussian-process factor analysis (GPFA) is a dimensionality reduction method[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35m:cite:`gpfa-Yu2008_1881` for neural trajectory visualization of parallel spike[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mtrains. GPFA applies factor analysis (FA) to time-binned spike count data to[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mreduce the dimensionality and at the same time smoothes the resulting[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mlow-dimensional trajectories by fitting a Gaussian process (GP) model to them.[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mThe input consists of a set of trials (Y), each containing a list of spike[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35mInternally, the analysis consists of the following steps:[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m78 | [0m[35m/**[0m
[30;1m79 | [0m[35m * Builds the next sequence_sorted, given the absolute iteration ID.[0m
[30;1m80 | [0m[35m * The time complexity is O(N+D), not O(N*D).[0m
[30;1m81 | [0m[35m *[0m
